	to
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Loan and security agreement
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	This Consent and First
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	Amendment to Loan and Security Agreement (this
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Amendment
</FONT>
	&#8221;) is entered into this 23
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	rd
</SUP>
	day of December, 2015, by and between
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	SILICON VALLEY BANK
</FONT>
	, a California corporation with a loan production office located at 275 Grove Street, Suite 2-200, Newton, Massachusetts 02466 (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Bank
</FONT>
	&#8221;), and
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	DIMENSION THERAPEUTICS, INC.
</FONT>
	, a Delaware corporation with an office located at 840 Memorial Drive, Cambridge, Massachusetts 02139 (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Borrower
</FONT>
	&#8221;).
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-VARIANT: SMALL-CAPS;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;">
	Recitals
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	A.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	Bank and Borrower have entered into that certain Loan and Security Agreement dated as of August 21, 2014, (as the same may from time to time be amended, modified, supplemented or restated, the &#8220;
</FONT>
	Loan Agreement
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	B.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	Bank has extended credit to Borrower for the purposes permitted in the Loan Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	C.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	Borrower has requested that Bank amend the Loan Agreement to make certain revisions to the Loan Agreement as more fully set forth herein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	D.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	Bank has agreed to so amend certain provisions of the Loan Agreement, but only to the extent, in accordance with the terms, subject to the conditions and in reliance upon the representations and warranties set forth below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-VARIANT: SMALL-CAPS;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;">
	Agreement
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-VARIANT: SMALL-CAPS;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;">
	Now, Therefore,
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	in consideration of the foregoing recitals and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which is hereby acknowledged, and intending to be legally bound, the parties hereto agree as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Definitions.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Capitalized terms used but not defined in this Amendment shall have the meanings given to them in the Loan Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Amendments to Loan Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 6.6 (Operating Accounts)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Section 6.6(a) is amended in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;MARGIN-RIGHT:7.69%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220; (a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Maintain all of its and all of its Subsidiaries&#8217; (excluding Securities Corp.) operating, depository and securities accounts with Bank and Bank&#8217;s Affiliates, provided, further, Borrower (individually and not on a consolidated basis) shall at all times have on deposit in operating, depository and securities accounts maintained with Bank or Bank&#8217;s Affiliates, cash in an amount equal to or greater than one hundred five percent (105.0%) of the then-outstanding Obligations of Borrower to Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bank may restrict withdrawals or transfers by or on behalf of Borrower that would violate this Section 6.6(a), regardless of whether an Event of Default exists at such time.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.2&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 7.7 (Distributions; Investments)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Section 7.7(b) is amended in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;MARGIN-RIGHT:7.69%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220; (b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;directly or indirectly make any Investment (including, without limitation, by the formation of any Subsidiary) other than Permitted Investments, or permit any of its Subsidiaries (other than Securities Corp.) to do so.&#8221;

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 13.1 (Definitions)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The definition of Permitted Investments as set forth in Section 13.1 of the Loan Agreement is amended by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	(i) deleting &#8220;and&#8221; at the end of subsection (e), (ii) deleting &#8220;.&#8221; at the end of subsection (f) and inserting &#8220;; and&#8221;, and (iii) inserting the following new subsection to appear as subsection (g) thereof:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;MARGIN-RIGHT:7.69%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220; (g) &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;cash Investments by Borrower in Securities Corp.; provided that no Event of Default has occurred and is continuing or would result from such Investment.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.4
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 13
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Definitions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	).&nbsp;&nbsp;The following terms and their respective definitions set forth in Section&#160;13.1 are amended in their entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;MARGIN-RIGHT:7.69%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220; &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Collateral Account
</FONT>
	&#8221; is any Deposit Account, Securities Account, or Commodity Account of Borrower.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;MARGIN-RIGHT:7.69%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220; &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Loan Documents
</FONT>
	&#8221; are, collectively, this Agreement and any schedules, exhibits, certificates, notices, and any other documents related to this Agreement, the Warrant, the Perfection Certificate, the Stock Pledge Agreement, any Bank Services Agreement, any subordination agreement, any note, or notes or guaranties executed by Borrower, and any other present or future agreement by Borrower with or for the benefit of Bank in connection with this Agreement or Bank Services, all as amended, restated, or otherwise modified.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.5
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

	Section 13

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Definitions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	).&nbsp;&nbsp;The following new terms and their definitions are inserted to appear alphabetically in Section&#160;13.1:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;MARGIN-RIGHT:7.69%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220; &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Pledge Agreement
</FONT>
	&#8221; means that certain Stock Pledge Agreement executed by Borrower in favor of Bank dated as of December 23, 2015, as may be amended, modified, supplemented or restated from time to time.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;MARGIN-RIGHT:7.69%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220; &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Securities Corp.
</FONT>
	&#8221; is Dimension Securities Corporation, a corporation organized under the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts and a Subsidiary of Borrower.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Limitation of Amendments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3.1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	The amendments set forth in Section&#160;2, above, are effective for the purposes set forth herein and shall be limited precisely as written and shall not be deemed to (a)&#160;be a consent to any amendment, waiver or modification of any other term or condition of any Loan Document, or (b)&#160;otherwise prejudice any right or remedy which Bank may now have or may have in the future under or in connection with any Loan Document.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3.2&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	This Amendment shall be construed in connection with and as part of the Loan Documents and all terms, conditions, representations, warranties, covenants and agreements set forth in the Loan Documents, except as herein amended, are hereby ratified and confirmed and shall remain in full force and effect.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Consent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Borrower has notified Bank that Borrower intends to create the Securities Corp. (the &#8220;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Subsidiary Formation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;Borrower has requested that Bank consent to the Subsidiary Formation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bank hereby consents to the Subsidiary Formation and agrees that the Subsidiary Formation shall not, in and of itself, constitute an &#8220;Event of Default&#8221; under Section 7.3 (relative to mergers or acquisitions), Section 7.7 (relative to distributions and Investments), or Section 7.8 (relative to transactions with Affiliates) of the Loan Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Borrower hereby acknowledges and agrees that nothing in this Section or anywhere in this Amendment shall be deemed or otherwise construed as a waiver by Bank of any of its rights and remedies pursuant to the Loan Documents, applicable law or otherwise.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage172"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Representations and Warranties.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;To induce Bank to enter into this Amendment, Borrower hereby represents and warrants to Bank as follows:
</FONT>
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	Immediately after giving effect to this Amendment (a)&#160;the representations and warranties contained in the Loan Documents are true, accurate and complete in all material respects as of the date hereof (except to the extent such representations and warranties relate to an earlier date, in which case they are true and correct in all material respects as of such date), and (b)&#160;no Event of Default has occurred and is continuing;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.2&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	Borrower has the power and authority to execute and deliver this Amendment and to perform its obligations under the Loan Agreement, as amended by this Amendment;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.3&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	The organizational documents of Borrower delivered to Bank on the Effective Date remain true, accurate and complete and have not been amended, supplemented or restated and are and continue to be in full force and effect;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.4&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	The execution and delivery by Borrower of this Amendment and the performance by Borrower of its obligations under the Loan Agreement, as amended by this Amendment, have been duly authorized;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.5&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	The execution and delivery by Borrower of this Amendment and the performance by Borrower of its obligations under the Loan Agreement, as amended by this Amendment, do not and will not contravene (a)&#160;any law or regulation binding on or affecting Borrower, (b)&#160;any contractual restriction with a Person binding on Borrower, (c)&#160;any order, judgment or decree of any court or other governmental or public body or authority, or subdivision thereof, binding on Borrower, or (d)&#160;the organizational documents of Borrower;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.6&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	The execution and delivery by Borrower of this Amendment and the performance by Borrower of its obligations under the Loan Agreement, as amended by this Amendment, do not require any order, consent, approval, license, authorization or validation of, or filing, recording or registration by Borrower with, or exemption by any governmental or public body or authority, or subdivision thereof, binding on Borrower, except as already has been obtained or made; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.7&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	This Amendment has been duly executed and delivered by Borrower and is the binding obligation of Borrower, enforceable against Borrower in accordance with its terms, except as such enforceability may be limited by bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization, liquidation, moratorium or other similar laws of general application and by general equitable principles.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	6.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Updated Perfection Certificate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Borrower has delivered an updated Perfection Certificate in connection with this Amendment dated as of even date hereof (the &#8220;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Updated Perfection Certificate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8221;), which Updated Perfection Certificate shall supersede in all respects that certain Perfection Certificate dated as of August 21, 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;Borrower agrees that all references in the Loan Agreement to &#8220;Perfection Certificate&#8221; shall hereinafter be deemed to be a reference to the Updated Perfection Certificate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	7.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Integration
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Amendment and the Loan Documents represent the entire agreement about this subject matter and supersede prior negotiations or agreements.&nbsp;&nbsp;All prior agreements, understandings, representations, warranties, and negotiations between the parties about the subject matter of this Amendment and the Loan Documents merge into this Amendment and the Loan Documents.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	8.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Counterparts.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;This Amendment may be executed in any number of counterparts and all of such counterparts taken together shall be deemed to constitute one and the same instrument.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	9.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:64PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Effectiveness
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Amendment shall be deemed effective upon (a) the due execution and delivery to Bank of this Amendment by each party hereto and (b)&#160;Borrower&#8217;s payment of Bank&#8217;s legal fees and expenses incurred in connection with this Amendment.
</FONT>
</P>

</TR>
<TR>

	Title:

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage174"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	SECOND AMENDMENT
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	TO
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	LOAN AND SECURITY AGREEMENT
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	This Second Amendment to Loan and Security Agreement (this
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#8220;Amendment&#8221;)
</FONT>
	is entered into this 9
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	day of February, 2016 by and between
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	SILICON VALLEY BANK (&#8220;Bank&#8221;)
</FONT>
	and
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	DIMENSION THERAPEUTICS, INC.,
</FONT>
	Delaware corporation
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	(&#8220;Borrower&#8221;)
</FONT>
	whose address is 840 Memorial Drive, Cambridge, Massachusetts 02139.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	R
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;">
	ECITALS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	A
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Bank and Borrower have entered into that certain Loan and Security Agreement dated as of August 21, 2014, as amended by that certain Consent and First Amendment to Loan and Security Agreement by and between Borrower and Bank dated as of December 23, 2015 (as the same may from time to time be further amended, modified, supplemented or restated, the &#8220;
</FONT>
	Loan Agreement
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&#8221;).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	B.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Bank has extended credit to Borrower for the purposes permitted in the Loan Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	C.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Borrower has requested that Bank amend the Loan Agreement to (i) extend a new equipment facility to Borrower, (ii) revise the financial reporting requirements and (iii) make certain other revisions to the Loan Agreement as more fully set forth herein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	D.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Bank has agreed to so amend certain provisions of the Loan Agreement, but only to the extent, in accordance with the terms, subject to the conditions and in reliance upon the representations and warranties set forth below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	A
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;">
	GREEMENT
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Now, T
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;">
	HEREFORE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	, in consideration of the foregoing recitals and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which is hereby acknowledged, and intending to be legally bound, the parties hereto agree as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1. Definitions.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Capitalized terms used but not defined in this Amendment shall have the meanings given to them in the Loan Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2. Amendments to Loan Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.1 Section 2.1.2 (2016 Equipment Advances).
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	The Loan Agreement is amended by inserting the following new provision to appear as Section 2.1.2 (2016 Equipment Advances) thereof:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.1.2 2016 Equipment Advances.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Availability
</FONT>
	. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, during the 2016 Draw Period, Bank shall make advances (each, a
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#8220;2016 Equipment Advance&#8221;
</FONT>
	and, collectively, the
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#8220;2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Equipment Advances&#8221;)
</FONT>
	not exceeding the 2016 Equipment Line. 2016 Equipment Advances may only be used to finance Eligible Equipment purchased within ninety (90) days (determined based upon the applicable invoice date of such Eligible Equipment) before the Funding Date of each 2016 Equipment Advance. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the initial 2016 Equipment Advance (the
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#8220;Initial 2016 Equipment Advance&#8221;)
</FONT>
	hereunder may be used to reimburse Borrower for Eligible Equipment purchased within six (6) months (determined based upon the applicable invoice date of such Eligible Equipment) before the 2016 Amendment Date. No 2016 Equipment Advance may exceed one hundred percent (100.0%) of the total invoice for Eligible Equipment (excluding taxes, shipping, warranty charges, freight discounts and installation expenses relating to such Eligible Equipment except to the extent such are allowed to be financed pursuant hereto as Other Equipment). Unless otherwise agreed to by Bank, not more than thirty percent (30.0%) of the proceeds of the 2016 Equipment Line shall be used to finance Other Equipment. Each 2016 Equipment Advance must be in an amount equal to at least the lesser of (i) Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($500,000.00) or (ii) the amount that has not yet been drawn under the 2016 Equipment Line. Borrower may only request four (4) 2016 Equipment Advances hereunder. After repayment, no 2016 Equipment Advance may be reborrowed.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage175"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Interest Period
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	. Commencing on the first (1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;">
	st
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	) Payment Date of the month following the month in which the Funding Date of the applicable 2016 Equipment Advance occurs and continuing on each Payment Date thereafter, Borrower shall make monthly payments of interest, in arrears, on the principal amount of each 2016 Equipment Advance at the rate set forth in Section 2.2(a)(ii).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(c)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Repayment
</FONT>
	. Commencing on the applicable 2016 Amortization Date, and continuing on the Payment Date of each month thereafter, Borrower shall repay each 2016 Equipment Advance in (i) thirty-six (36) equal monthly installments of principal, plus (ii) monthly payments of accrued interest at the rate set forth in Section 2.2(a)(ii). All outstanding principal and accrued interest under each 2016 Equipment Advance, and all other outstanding Obligations with respect to each 2016 Equipment Advance, is due and payable in full on the applicable 2016 Equipment Maturity Date.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(d)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Mandatory Prepayment Upon an Acceleration
</FONT>
	. If repayment of the 2016 Equipment Advances is accelerated by Bank following the occurrence and during the continuance of an Event of Default, Borrower shall immediately pay to Bank an amount equal to the sum of: (i) all outstanding principal plus accrued and unpaid interest, (ii) the 2016 Prepayment Premium, (iii) the 2016 Final Payment, plus (iv) all other sums, if any, that shall have become due and payable hereunder with respect to the 2016 Equipment Advances, including interest at the Default Rate with respect to any past due amounts.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(e)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Permitted Prepayment of 2016 Equipment Advances
</FONT>
	. Borrower shall have the option to prepay all, but not less than all, of the 2016 Equipment Advances advanced by Bank under this Agreement, provided Borrower (i) provides written notice to Bank of its election to prepay the 2016 Equipment Advances at least five (5) days prior to such prepayment, and (ii) pays, on the date of such prepayment (A) all outstanding principal plus accrued and unpaid interest, (B) the 2016 Prepayment Premium, (C) the 2016 Final Payment, plus (D) all other sums, if any, that shall have become due and payable hereunder with respect to the 2016 Equipment Advances, including interest at the Default Rate with respect to any past due amounts.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.2 Section 2.2(a) (Interest Rate).
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Section 2.2(a) is amended in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Interest Rate
</FONT>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(i) Subject to Section 2.2(b), the principal amount outstanding for each Equipment Advance shall accrue interest at a fixed per annum rate equal to two and one quarter of one percent (2.25%) above the Prime Rate, which interest shall be determined by Bank on the Funding Date of the applicable Equipment Advance and shall be payable monthly in arrears in accordance with Section 2.2(c) below.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(ii) Subject to Section 2.2(b), the principal amount outstanding for each 2016 Equipment Advance shall accrue interest at a fixed per annum rate equal to one half of one percent (0.50%) below the Prime Rate, which interest shall be determined by Bank on the Funding Date of the applicable 2016 Equipment Advance and shall be payable monthly in arrears in accordance with Section 2.2(c) below.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.3 Section 2.3 (Fees).
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Section 2.3 is amended in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.3 Fees.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Borrower shall pay to Bank:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Commitment Fee
</FONT>
	. A fully earned, non-refundable commitment fee of Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), was paid on the Effective Date;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Prepayment Premium
</FONT>
	. The Prepayment Premium, when due hereunder;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(c)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	2016 Prepayment Premium
</FONT>
	. The 2016 Prepayment Premium, when due hereunder;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(d)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	2016 Final Payment
</FONT>
	. The 2016 Final Payment, when due hereunder;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(e)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Good Faith Deposit
</FONT>
	. Borrower has paid to Bank a deposit of Fifteen Thousand Dollars ($15,000.00) (the
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#8220;Good Faith Deposit&#8221;)
</FONT>
	to initiate Bank&#8217;s due diligence review process. The Good Faith Deposit shall be utilized to pay Bank Expenses.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(f)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Bank Expenses
</FONT>
	. All Bank Expenses (including reasonable attorneys&#8217; fees and expenses for documentation and negotiation of this Agreement) incurred through and after the Effective Date, when due (or, if no stated due date, upon demand by Bank).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<A NAME="eolPage176"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(g)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Fees Fully Earned
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	. Unless otherwise provided in this Agreement or in a separate writing by Bank, Borrower shall not be entitled to any credit, rebate, or repayment of any fees earned by Bank pursuant to this Agreement notwithstanding any termination of this Agreement or the suspension or termination of Bank&#8217;s obligation to make loans and advances hereunder. Bank may deduct amounts owing by Borrower under the clauses of this Section 2.3 pursuant to the terms of Section 2.4(c). Bank shall provide Borrower written notice of deductions made from the Designated Deposit Account pursuant to the terms of the clauses of this Section 2.3.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.4
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
</FONT>
	Section 6.2(a) (Quarterly Financial Statements).
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Section 6.2(a) is deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Quarterly Financial Statements
</FONT>
	. As soon as available, but no later than forty-five (45) days after the last day of each quarter, a company prepared consolidated balance sheet and income statement covering Borrower&#8217;s consolidated operations for such quarter certified by a Responsible Officer and in a form acceptable to Bank (the
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#8220;Quarterly Financial Statements&#8221;);
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.5 Section 6.2(b) (Quarterly Compliance Certificate).
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Section 6.2(b) is deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(d)
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Quarterly Compliance Certificate
</FONT>
	. Within forty-five (45) days after the last day of each quarter and together with the Quarterly Financial Statements, a duly completed Compliance Certificate signed by a Responsible Officer, certifying that as of the end of such quarter, Borrower was in full compliance with all of the terms and conditions of this Agreement and such other information as Bank may reasonably request;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.6 Section 6.2(c) (Board Projections).
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Section 6.2(c) is amended by deleting the words &#8220;sixty (60)&#8221; appearing therein and inserting in lieu thereof the words &#8220;forty-five (45)&#8221;.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.7
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
</FONT>
	Section 6.2(d) (Annual Audited Financial Statements).
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Section 6.2(d) is amended by deleting the words &#8220;one hundred eighty (180) days after the last day of Borrower&#8217;s fiscal year&#8221; appearing therein and inserting in lieu thereof the words &#8220;one hundred fifty (150) days after the last day of Borrower&#8217;s fiscal year, and contemporaneously with any filing of such statements with the SEC, and at least annually,&#8221;.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.8
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.10 Section 13 (Definitions).
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	The following terms and their respective definitions set forth in Section 13.1 are amended in their entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;Credit Extension&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is any Equipment Advance, 2016 Equipment Advance or any other extension of credit by Bank for Borrower&#8217;s benefit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;Eligible Equipment&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is the following to the extent it complies with all of Borrower&#8217;s representations and warranties to Bank, is acceptable to Bank in all respects, is located at 840 Memorial Drive, Cambridge, Massachusetts 02139, 19 Presidential Way, Woburn, Massachusetts 01801, or such other location of which Bank has approved in writing, and is subject to a first priority Lien in favor of Bank: (a) for the Equipment Advances, (i) new and used general purpose equipment, computer equipment, office equipment, test and laboratory equipment, furnishings, subject to the limitations set forth herein, and (ii) Other Equipment; and (b) for the 2016 Equipment Advances, (i) new and used computer equipment, office equipment, laboratory equipment, research equipment and process development equipment, subject to the limitations set forth herein, and (ii) Other Equipment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;Equipment Maturity Date&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is, for each Equipment Advance, the date which is thirty-five (35) months after the applicable Amortization Date for such Equipment Advance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;Obligations&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	are Borrower&#8217;s obligations to pay when due any debts, principal, interest, fees, Bank Expenses, the Prepayment Premium, the 2016 Final Payment, the 2016 Prepayment Premium, and other amounts Borrower owes Bank now or later, whether under this Agreement, the other Loan Documents (other than the Warrant), or otherwise, including, without limitation, any interest accruing after Insolvency Proceedings begin and debts, liabilities, or obligations of Borrower assigned to Bank, and to perform Borrower&#8217;s duties under the Loan Documents (other than the Warrant).
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	The Loan Agreement is amended by inserting the following new terms and their respective definitions to appear alphabetically in Section 13.1:

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Amendment Date&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is February 9, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Amortization Date&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	means, for each 2016 Equipment Advance, the first (1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	st
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	) Payment Date following the six (6) month anniversary of the Funding Date of such 2016 Equipment Advance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Draw Period&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	means the period of time commencing upon the 2016 Amendment Date and continuing through the earlier to occur of (a) June 30, 2017 or (b) an Event of Default.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Equipment Advance&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	and &#8220;
</FONT>
	2016 Equipment Advances
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&#8221; are defined in Section 2.1.2(a).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Equipment Line&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is a 2016 Equipment Advance or 2016 Equipment Advances in an aggregate principal amount of up to Seven Million Dollars ($7,000,000.00).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Equipment Maturity Date&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is, for each 2016 Equipment Advance, the date which is thirty-five (35) months after the applicable 2016 Amortization Date for such 2016 Equipment Advance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Final Payment&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is a payment (in addition to and not a substitution for the regular monthly payments of principal plus accrued interest) equal to the original principal amount of each 2016 Equipment Advance extended by Bank to Borrower multiplied by the 2016 Final Payment Percentage, due on the earliest to occur of (a) the applicable 2016 Equipment Maturity Date, (b) the acceleration by Bank of the 2016 Equipment Advances pursuant to Section 9.1, (c) the prepayment by Borrower of the 2016 Equipment Advances pursuant to Section 2.1.2(d) or 2.1.2(e), or (d) the termination of this Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Final Payment Percentage&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is, for each 2016 Equipment Advance, six percent (6.0%).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;2016 Prepayment Premium&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is an additional fee payable to the Bank in amount equal to:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a) for a prepayment of the 2016 Equipment Advances made on or prior to the second (2
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;">
	nd
</FONT>
	) anniversary of the 2016 Amendment Date, one percent (1.0%) of the principal amount of the 2016 Equipment Advances outstanding as of the date immediately and prior to such prepayment; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b) for a prepayment of the 2016 Equipment Advances made after the second (2
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;">
	nd
</FONT>
	) anniversary of the 2016 Amendment Date, zero percent (0.0%) of the principal amount of the 2016 Equipment Advances outstanding as of the date immediately and prior to such prepayment.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Notwithstanding the foregoing, Bank agrees to waive the 2016 Prepayment Premium if Bank closes on the refinance and redocumentation of the 2016 Equipment Advances under another division of Bank (in its sole and absolute discretion) prior to the applicable 2016 Equipment Maturity Date.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;Good Faith Deposit&#8221;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is defined in Section 2.3(e).

<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	is defined in Section 2.1.2(a).

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

	means the Equipment Maturity Date and/or the 2016 Equipment Maturity Date, as applicable.

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3. Limitation of Amendments.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3.1
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	The amendments set forth in Section 2 above are effective for the purposes set forth herein and shall be limited precisely as written and shall not be deemed to (a) be a consent to any amendment, waiver or modification of any other term or condition of any Loan Document, or (b) otherwise prejudice any right or remedy which Bank may now have or may have in the future under or in connection with any Loan Document.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3.2
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	This Amendment shall be construed in connection with and as part of the Loan Documents and all terms, conditions, representations, warranties, covenants and agreements set forth in the Loan Documents, except as herein amended, are hereby ratified and confirmed and shall remain in full force and effect.

	4. Representations and Warranties
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. To induce Bank to enter into this Amendment, Borrower hereby represents and warrants to Bank as follows:

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.1
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Immediately after giving effect to this Amendment (a) the representations and warranties contained in the Loan Documents are true, accurate and complete in all material respects as of the date hereof (except to the extent such representations and warranties relate to an earlier date, in which case they are true and correct in all material respects as of such date), and (b) no Event of Default has occurred and is continuing;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.2
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Borrower has the power and authority to execute and deliver this Amendment and to perform its obligations under the Loan Agreement, as amended by this Amendment;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.3
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	The organizational documents of Borrower delivered to Bank on the Effective Date remain true, accurate and complete and have not been amended, supplemented or restated and are and continue to be in full force and effect;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.4
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	The execution and delivery by Borrower of this Amendment and the performance by Borrower of its obligations under the Loan Agreement, as amended by this Amendment, have been duly authorized;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.5
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	The execution and delivery by Borrower of this Amendment and the performance by Borrower of its obligations under the Loan Agreement, as amended by this Amendment, do not and will not contravene (a) any law or regulation binding on or affecting Borrower, (b) any contractual restriction with a Person binding on Borrower, (c) any order, judgment or decree of any court or other governmental or public body or authority, or subdivision thereof, binding on Borrower, or (d) the organizational documents of Borrower;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.6
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	The execution and delivery by Borrower of this Amendment and the performance by Borrower of its obligations under the Loan Agreement, as amended by this Amendment, do not require any order, consent, approval, license, authorization or validation of, or filing, recording or registration with, or exemption by any governmental or public body or authority, or subdivision thereof, binding on Borrower, except as already has been obtained or made; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.7
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	This Amendment has been duly executed and delivered by Borrower and is the binding obligation of Borrower, enforceable against Borrower in accordance with its terms, except as such enforceability may be limited by bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization, liquidation, moratorium or other similar laws of general application and by general equitable principles.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5. Ratification of Stock Pledge Agreement.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Borrower hereby ratifies, confirms and reaffirms, all and singular, the terms and conditions of a certain Stock Pledge Agreement dated as of December 23, 2015 between Borrower and Bank (the
</FONT>
	&#8220;Stock Pledge Agreement&#8221;),
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	and acknowledges, confirms and agrees that the Stock Pledge Agreement (a) contains an accurate and complete listing of all Shares (as defined in the Stock Pledge Agreement), and (b) shall remain in full force and effect. Borrower hereby grants Bank, to secure the payment and performance in full of all the Obligations and the performance of each of Borrower&#8217;s duties under the Loan Documents, a continuing security interest in, and pledges to Bank, the Pledged Collateral (as defined in the Stock Pledge Agreement), wherever located, whether now owned or hereafter acquired or arising, and all proceeds and products thereof.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	6. Ratification of Perfection Certificate
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Borrower hereby ratifies, confirms and reaffirms, all and singular, the terms and disclosures contained in a certain Perfection Certificate dated as of December 23, 2015 between Borrower and Bank, and acknowledges, confirms and agrees the disclosures and information Borrower provided to Bank in said Perfection Certificate have not changed, as of the date hereof.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	7. Integration.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	This Amendment and the Loan Documents represent the entire agreement about this subject matter and supersede prior negotiations or agreements. All prior agreements, understandings, representations, warranties, and negotiations between the parties about the subject matter of this Amendment and the Loan Documents merge into this Amendment and the Loan Documents.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	8.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
</FONT>
	Counterparts.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	This Amendment may be executed in any number of counterparts and all of such counterparts taken together shall be deemed to constitute one and the same instrument.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	9.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
</FONT>
	Effectiveness.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	This Amendment shall be deemed effective upon (a) the due execution and delivery to Bank of this Amendment by each party hereto and (b) Borrower&#8217;s payment of Bank&#8217;s legal fees and expenses incurred in connection with this Amendment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	[Signature page follows.]
</P>

	&nbsp;
</P>

	The undersigned authorized officer of DIMENSION THERAPEUTICS, INC. (&#8220;Borrower&#8221;) certifies that under the terms and conditions of the Loan and Security Agreement between Borrower and Bank (the &#8220;Agreement&#8221;):

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(1) Borrower is in compliance for the period ending&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;with all required covenants except as noted below; (2) there are no Events of Default; (3) all representations and warranties in the Agreement are true and correct in all material respects on this date except as noted below; provided, however, that such materiality qualifier shall not be applicable to any representations and warranties that already are qualified or modified by materiality in the text thereof; and provided, further that those representations and warranties expressly referring to a specific date shall be true, accurate and complete in all material respects as of such date; (4) Borrower, and each of its Subsidiaries, has timely filed all required tax returns and reports, and Borrower has timely paid all foreign, federal, state and local taxes, assessments, deposits and contributions owed by Borrower except as otherwise permitted pursuant to the terms of Section 5.8 of the Agreement; and (5) no Liens have been levied or claims made against Borrower or any of its Subsidiaries relating to unpaid employee payroll or benefits of which Borrower has not previously provided written notification to Bank.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Attached are the required documents supporting the certification. The undersigned certifies that these are prepared in accordance with GAAP consistently applied from one period to the next except as explained in an accompanying letter or footnotes. The undersigned acknowledges that no borrowings may be requested at any time or date of determination that Borrower is not in compliance with any of the terms of the Agreement, and that compliance is determined not just at the date this certificate is delivered. Capitalized terms used but not otherwise defined herein shall have the meanings given them in the Agreement.
</P>

	Please indicate compliance status by circling Yes/No under &#8220;Complies&#8221; column.

	Exhibit&#160;31.1

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Certifications
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	I, Annalisa Jenkins, certify that:
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	1.
</FONT>
	I have reviewed this Annual Report on Form 10-K of Dimension Therapeutics, Inc.;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	2.
</FONT>
	Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	3.
</FONT>
	Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	4.
</FONT>
	The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer(s) and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) for the registrant and have:
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:11.47%;TEXT-INDENT:0.06%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	(a)
</FONT>
	Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:11.47%;TEXT-INDENT:0.06%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	(b)
</FONT>
	(Paragraph omitted pursuant to SEC Release Nos. 33-8238/34-47986 and 33-8392/34-49313);
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:11.47%;TEXT-INDENT:0.06%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	(c)
</FONT>
	Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#8217;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:11.47%;TEXT-INDENT:0.06%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	(d)
</FONT>
	Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#8217;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	5.
</FONT>
	The registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer(s) and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the registrant&#8217;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#8217;s board of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:11.47%;TEXT-INDENT:0.06%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	(a)
</FONT>
	All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the registrant&#8217;s ability to record, process, summarize and report financial information; and
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:11.47%;TEXT-INDENT:0.06%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	(b)
</FONT>
	Any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0PT;PADDING-TOP:0PT;WIDTH:60%; BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID 0.75PT TRANSPARENT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:7.2PT;;TEXT-INDENT:-7.2PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0PT;PADDING-TOP:0PT;WIDTH:2%; BORDER-BOTTOM:SOLID 0.75PT TRANSPARENT;">
